<p>Former Japanese prime minister Tomiichi Murayama died on Friday at a hospital in Oita City at the age of 101, according to Japan’s Social Democratic Party leadership [thehindu.com#1][abc.net.au#1][dawn.com#1]. Murayama, who led Japan from 1994 to 1996, is best known for a landmark 1995 statement marking the 50th anniversary of Japan’s World War II surrender that apologized for colonial rule and wartime aggression [reuters.com#1][nytimes.com#1][npr.org#1]. His declaration set enduring parameters for how subsequent leaders addressed wartime history [reuters.com#1][scmp.com#1].</p><img src='https://kagiproxy.com/img/b9TCvv58bWoQss1AkcVd1VwKzqqv5IW0x5HgDHQDQJXQ3TFXida_ArNEM15EdA9xOFG9jvnp601-IZ61PRk_sGlg7FScwURXVBQ1tZz3Fa7lKFFYuFU_hIdt4MDND7JPP2bE3JDwmBChA2rnwcImWFykuTC9Lxuvq_wRcuaOalq6Zg' alt='Prime Minister Tomiichi Murayama in 1995, the year he delivered his landmark apology.' /><br /><h3>Highlights:</h3><ul><li>Cross-party coalition: Murayama, a Socialist, governed in 1994–1996 atop a coalition with the conservative Liberal Democratic Party, an unusual arrangement in postwar Japanese politics [reuters.com#1][scmp.com#1].</li><li>Televised address: The apology was delivered in a nationally televised address that framed Japan’s official expression of remorse for wartime atrocities [nytimes.com#1].</li><li>Legacy language: Successors echoed Murayama’s wording during later World War II anniversaries, reinforcing its role in official commemorations [abc.net.au#1][dawn.com#1].</li><li>Cause reported: A local Social Democratic Party official in Oita said Murayama died of old age [dawn.com#1].</li></ul><blockquote>I regard, in a spirit of humility, these irrefutable facts of history, and express here once again my feelings of deep remorse and state my heartfelt apology. - Tomiichi Murayama</blockquote><h3>Perspectives:</h3><ul><li>Mizuho Fukushima (Social Democratic Party, Japan): Announced Murayama’s passing and called him “the father of Japanese politics,” underscoring his influence within the party. (<a href='https://www.dawn.com/news/1949501/japan-ex-pm-tomiichi-murayama-famous-for-ww2-apology-dies-aged-101'>Dawn</a>)</li><li>South China Morning Post: Highlights that Murayama presided over a turbulent period that included a devastating 1995 earthquake and the Tokyo subway sarin attack. (<a href='https://www.scmp.com/news/asia/east-asia/article/3329360/japan-ex-pm-murayama-who-apologised-wwii-aggression-dies-101'>South China Morning Post</a>)</li></ul><h3>Sources:</h3><ul><li><a href='https://www.thehindu.com/news/international/former-japanese-prime-minister-murayama-known-for-apology-over-wartime-aggression-dies-at-101/article70174519.ece'>Former Japanese Prime Minister Murayama, known for apology over wartime aggression, dies at 101</a> - thehindu.com</li><li><a href='https://www.nytimes.com/2025/10/17/world/asia/tomiichi-murayama-dead.html'>Tomiichi Murayama, Japanese Leader Who Gave War Apology, Dies at 101</a> - nytimes.com</li><li><a href='https://www.npr.org/2025/10/17/nx-s1-5577652/japanese-pm-murayama-dead'>Former Japanese PM Murayama, known for apology over wartime aggression, dies at 101</a> - npr.org</li><li><a href='https://www.abc.net.au/news/2025-10-17/ex-japan-prime-minister-tomiichi-murayama-dies-aged-101/105906158'>Former Japanese PM Murayama, famous for WWII apology, dies aged 101</a> - abc.net.au</li><li><a href='https://www.scmp.com/news/asia/east-asia/article/3329360/japan-ex-pm-murayama-who-apologised-wwii-aggression-dies-101'>Japan ex-PM Murayama, who apologised for WWII aggression, dies at 101</a> - scmp.com</li><li><a href='https://www.reuters.com/world/asia-pacific/obituary-socialist-pm-murayama-issued-landmark-apology-japans-wartime-deeds-2025-10-17/'>OBITUARY Socialist PM Murayama issued landmark apology for Japan&#x27;s wartime deeds</a> - reuters.com</li><li><a href='https://www.dawn.com/news/1949501/japan-ex-pm-tomiichi-murayama-famous-for-ww2-apology-dies-aged-101'>Japan ex-PM Tomiichi Murayama, 